# Prevent "bytes are not valid utf8" failures in Git clients (e.g. VS Code's
# commit-message generator) that decode `git diff` output as UTF-8.
#
# Line-delimited data/log dumps and certain generated artifacts can contain
# non-UTF-8 bytes (e.g. Windows-1252). Marking them `-diff` makes Git emit
# "Binary files ... differ" instead of the raw bytes, keeping every diff valid
# UTF-8 without altering file contents.
*.jsonl                          -diff
*.ndjson                         -diff
goose-releases.jsonl             -diff
backend/html-chunker/output.txt  -diff
